- If the specified value is outside this range, **MuteTime** defaults to **10000**.
- This parameter can be dynamically updated during the call. The last set value takes effect.', example='10000'),
  outId?: string(name='OutId', description='An ID reserved for the caller. This ID will be returned to the caller in the receipt message.  
It is a string with a length of 1 to 15 bytes.', example='222356****'),
  ownerId?: long(name='OwnerId'),
  pauseTime?: int32(name='PauseTime', description='Pause duration. Specifies how long the user must pause to indicate the end of a sentence. Unit: milliseconds. Valid range: **300–1200**.

